	  </d:refnamediv>


	  <d:refsynopsisdiv>
      <x:div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:x="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
         <x:h1>Command xgrep</x:h1>

   
         <x:h3>Name</x:h3>

         <x:strong>xgrep</x:strong> Find patterns in XML files<x:br/>
   
         <x:h3>Synopsis</x:h3>

xgrep expr [files]<x:br/>

         <x:table class="data">
            <x:tbody>
               <x:tr>
                  <x:td>expr</x:td>
                  <x:td>an XPath expression to search</x:td>
               </x:tr>
               <x:tr>
                  <x:td>[files]	</x:td>
                  <x:td>List of files to search</x:td>
               </x:tr>
            </x:tbody>
         </x:table>
         <x:br/>
   
         <x:h3>Description</x:h3>

         <x:br/>
xgrep parses each xml file given and if it contains a node which matches the xpath expression (expr) prints the filename of the matching file.<x:br/>
         <x:br/>
Example:<x:br/>
         <x:div class="code">
            <x:pre>xgrep '//foo'  *.xml</x:pre>
         </x:div>

   
         <x:h3>Return Value</x:h3>

Returns 0 if the command executed successfully, 1 if there was an error.<x:br/>


 
         <x:br/>


      </x:div>
